level_1.name: Cure Light Wounds
level_1.note:
creature touched
When laying your hand upon a living creature, you channel positive energy that cures 1d8 points of damage +1 point per caster level (maximum +5). Since undead are powered by negative energy, this spell deals damage to them instead of curing their wounds. An undead creature can apply Spell Resistance, and can attempt a Will save to take half damage.

character.note:
Favour Class
Half-Elf     Add +¼ to the number of times per day the inquisitor can change her most recent teamwork feat.
Human     Add one spell known from the inquisitor spell list. This spell must be at least one level below the highest spell level the inquisitor can cast.
Elf     Add one spell known from the inquisitor’s spell list. This spell must be at least one level below the highest-level spell the inquisitor can cast.

Defense Racial Traits

    Elven Immunities: Half-elves are immune to magic sleep effects and gain a +2 racial saving throw bonus against enchantment spells and effects.

Feat and Skill Racial Traits

    Adaptability: Half-elves receive Skill Focus as a bonus feat at 1st level.
    Keen Senses: Half-elves receive a +2 racial bonus on Perception checks.

Senses Racial Traits

    Low-Light Vision: Half-elves can see twice as far as humans in conditions of dim light.

Other Racial Traits

    Elf Blood: Half-elves count as both elves and humans for any effect related to race.
    Multitalented: Half-elves choose two favored classes at first level and gain +1 hit point or +1 skill point whenever they take a level in either one of those classes.

story.note:
Iron Gods:
My story is one of companionship and hardship. I am from a small village, Erages of Kyonin. Just beyond the reach of the River Kingdoms. I was raised there, by others of my kind, separated from the influence of the high elves.
I, like most of my kind, realize the burden we place on nature and thank her for her bounty. It is my sworn duty to Erastil to protect nature from those that would do her harm.
I ventured far from my home, to far-away lands of Numeria, to explore the world and make an impact. I protected the villagers of Ladenveigh by hunting the spiders of Echo Woods for years. Now the villagers are able to care for their own, learning how to combat the threats.
While there, the villagers told me stories of syndicate groups fighting for control, destroying the surrounding lands and punishing those that disobey them. So I travelled to Torch where I heard a gathering is taking place...
